Working with the RAID configurations on Linux can be a little involved if all you have is hpacucli. Luckily, the folks using HP&rsquo;s OS distributions will get tools like hwraidinfo and hwraid status, but you can get these going in Linux as well.
Here&rsquo;s a bash script equivalent of hwraidinfo which will work in Linux:
#!/bin/sh SLOTLIST=$(hpacucli ctrl all show | \ grep Slot | sed -e 's/^.*Slot //g' -e 's/ .
